properties.id: The ID of the price list rule.
properties.attribute: The attribute of the price list rule. For example, `region_id`.
properties.value: The value of the price list rule. For example, `reg_123`.

properties.id: The ID of the price list.
properties.title: The title of the price list.
properties.description: The description of the price list.
properties.status: The status of the price list.
properties.type: The type of the price list.
properties.starts_at: The date the price list starts.
properties.ends_at: The date the price list ends.
properties.rules_count: The total number of rules of the price list.

properties.id: The ID of the price rule.
properties.attribute: The attribute of the price rule. For example, `region_id`.
properties.value: The value of the price rule. For example, `reg_123`.
properties.operator: The operator of the price rule. For example, `eq`.
properties.priority: The priority of the price rule.

properties.id: The ID of the price set.

properties.title: The title of the price
properties.currency_code: The currency code of the price. For example, `usd`.
properties.min_quantity: The minimum quantity that must be available in the cart for the price to be applied.
properties.max_quantity: The maximum quantity allowed to be available in the cart for the price to be applied.
properties.rules_count: The total number of rules of the price.

properties.id: The ID of the price preference.
properties.attribute: The attribute of the price preference. For example, `region_id`.
properties.value: The value of the price preference. For example, `reg_123`.
properties.is_tax_inclusive: Whether prices matching this preference include taxes.
